snippet.title: ZTE Open C
snippet.description: At MWC this year, ZTE showcased its 3G Open C handset, which will run Firefox OS 1.3.

snippet.title: ZTE Open II
snippet.description: The Open II features a 2-megapixel camera and Firefox OS, and has its sights on emerging markets.

snippet.title: ZTE Open
snippet.description: Skip the ZTE Open and keep hunting for your low-cost smartphone, unless simplicity or Firefox development are at the top of your list.

snippet.title: Cracking Open the Amazon Fire TV
snippet.description: Bill Detwiler cracks open the Amazon Fire TV and gives you a tour inside Amazon's first streaming media box.

snippet.title: Psystar Open Computer
snippet.description: Its hardware isn't made by Apple's design team, it will likely never work as a full member of the greater Apple ecosystem, and one ill-intended software update could turn it into a $750 brick. Get past all of that, and you'll find Psystar's OS X-based Open Computer a fast and otherwise compelling lower midrange desktop.

snippet.title: 2015 BMW M4 Convertible
snippet.description: At the New York auto show, BMW presented the all-new M4 with a retractable hard top.

snippet.title: Yes, Android is a free and open platform but...
snippet.description: Google imposes certain terms on phone and tablet manufacturers in return for key apps on that free operating system, says The Wall Street Journal.

snippet.title: Heartbleed coder admits 'oversight' but backs open source
snippet.description: The programmer who inadvertently introduced the Heartbleed bug to the Internet on New Year's Eve 2011 reckons the fact it was eventually spotted proves the value of open source.

snippet.title: Samsung-branded stores open in time for Galaxy S5
snippet.description: The Samsung Galaxy S5 hits shops Friday, and Samsung has opened more branded stores today to celebrate the new phone.
